early%20550%2C000%20were%20working%20into%20their%2080s%20and%20beyond%20as%20of%202023%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Business%20Insider%20analysis%20of%202023%20Census%20data.%20That's%20over%204%25%20of%20the%20population%20aged%2080%20and%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20more%20than%20175%20people%2080%20and%20older%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%20working%20later%20in%20life%2C%20most%20mentioned%20some%20health%20issue%20as%20a%20challenge.%20Common%20ones%20included%20arthritis%2C%20mobility%20impairments%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhabits-that-look-healthy-heart-disease-failure-stroke-inflammation-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eheart%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20hearing%20loss%2C%20and%20memory%20problems.%20Most%20of%20these%20didn't%20prevent%20them%20from%20performing%20their%20job%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20said%20their%20conditions%20were%20severe%20enough%20that%20they%20would%20have%20retired%20years%20ago%20if%20they%20could%20have%2C%20though%20they%20need%20to%20work%20to%20pay%20their%20bills.%20Their%20health%20issues%20have%20led%20them%20to%20either%20struggle%20throughout%20the%20day%20or%20find%20employment%20where%20they%20can%20work%20around%20periods%20of%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20four%20decades%2C%20Patricia%20Moore%2C%2081%2C%20has%20managed%20a%20gas%20station%2C%20earning%20about%20%2436%2C000%20a%20year%20despite%20suffering%20from%20neuropathy%20and%20swelling.%20It's%20exhausting%20some%20days%2C%20but%20she%20has%20to%20work%20to%20supplement%20her%20%242%2C800%20monthly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F90-still-work-retirement-social-security-job-training-lower-income-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20income%2C%20as%20she%20doesn't%20have%20sufficient%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRetirement%20is%20not%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20as%20it%20costs%20more%20every%20month%20to%20just%20survive%