You'd%20ask%20the%20question%2C%20like%2C%20'Why%20are%20they%20interested%20in%20venture%3F'%20and%20usually%20when%20I%20meet%20people%20like%20that%2C%20the%20answers%20are%20pretty%20superficial.%20Most%20people%20don't%20even%20understand%20what%20venture%20really%20is%20versus%20what%20it%20looks%20like%20on%20TV%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERabois%20said%20it's%20essential%20for%20newcomers%20to%20either%20learn%20how%20to%20build%20their%20own%20companies%20or%20watch%20others%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFirst%20of%20all%2C%20it'll%20make%20you%20more%20confident%20that%20you're%20making%20the%20right%20decision.%20This%20is%20a%2020-year%20job%20minimum.%20Secondly%2C%20you'll%20be%20better%20suited%20to%20perform%20the%20job.%20And%20third%2C%20you'll%20have%20more%20credibility%2C%20which%20also%20helps%20you%20perform%20the%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Rabois%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERabois%20is%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20Khosla%20Ventures%20and%20has%20served%20on%20the%20boards%20of%20several%20companies%2C%20including%20Reddit%20and%20Yelp.%20He's%20also%20the%20cofounder%20and%20chairman%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopendoor-keith-rabois-headcount-slashed-end-remote-work-dei-2025-9%3Futm_source%3Dflipboard%26utm_content%3Dtopic%252Fdiversity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpendoor%20Technologies%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20podcast%20interview%2C%20Rabois%20said%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20idea%26quot%3B%20for%20new%20graduates%20to%20want%20to%20become%20venture%20capitalists%20right%20after%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoesn't%20mean%20you%20can't%20be%20an%20associate%20somewhere.%20You%20know%2C%20spend%20two%20years%20watching%20and%20learning%2C%20A%3A%20Is%20this%20right%20for%20me%3F%20Because%20you'll%20see%20how%20the%20industry%20really%20works%2C%26quot%3B%20Rabois%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%2C%20use%20the%20platform%20and%20vantage%20point%20of%20